      <hedline>
        <hl1>A 12-Year-Old Boy, Killed in Gaza</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Earle B Hoyt Jr letter deplores horrific killing of 12-year-old boy in Gaza, expressing hope that it marks 'beginning of forgiveness and the end of killing'</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Nabil Aburdaineh, a senior adviser to Yasir Arafat, responds to the horrific killing of a 12-year-old Palestinian boy by saying, ''This cannot be forgiven'' (front page, Oct. 1).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Nabil Aburdaineh, a senior adviser to Yasir Arafat, responds to the horrific killing of a 12-year-old Palestinian boy by saying, ''This cannot be forgiven'' (front page, Oct. 1).</p>
        <p>If only the killing of Muhammad al-Durrah marked the beginning of forgiveness and the end of killing, particularly of children.</p>
        <p>EARLE B. HOYT JR.  Flagstaff, Ariz., Oct. 1, 2000</p>
      </block>
